\int_{-1}^1 2 - |x| = 3
-3
f(x) = 2 - |x|, f(x) \text{ is even function}
\int_{-1}^1f(x) = 2 \int_0^1 f(x) = 2 \int_0^1 2 - x = 2\bigg(\bigg|_0^12x-\frac{x^2}{2}  \bigg) = 2\bigg(0 - (2 - \frac{1}{2}) \bigg) = 2(-1.5) = -3.
f(x)\Big|_a^b=f(b)-f(a)
f(x)=2-|x|
I=[-1,1]
\int_If(x)dx=2\int_0^1(2-x)dx
2>|x|
x\in [-1,1]
2\int_0^1 2-x \, dx = 2\left[2x-\dfrac{x^2}{2}\right]_0^1 = 2\left[\left(2(1)-\dfrac{1^2}{2}\right) - \left(2(0)-\dfrac{0^2}{2}\right)\right] = 3
